From: Murray S. Kucherawy <msk@opendkim.org>
To: opendkim-announce@lists.opendkim.org, opendkim-users@lists.opendkim.org
Subject: OpenDKIM v2.6.8 released

The Trusted Domain Project announces availability of OpenDKIM v2.6.8, now
available for download from SourceForge.

This is a security release.  It places restrictions on the use of keys that
are small enough that they can be compromised within a small period of time.

The full RELEASE_NOTES for this version:

2.6.8		2012/10/24
	Add "MinimumKeyBits" configuration file item.
	LIBOPENDKIM: Feature request #SF3559744: Add library option
		DKIM_OPTS_MINKEYBITS allowing one to specify a minimum
		number of key bits for acceptable signatures.

Please use the mailing lists at http://lists.opendkim.org/ to report problems.
Bug reports and feature requests can be made through the project trackers,
which can be found via http://www.opendkim.org.

The Trusted Domain Project
